The paper deals with symbolic dynamics, which is a subfield of computer science that studies discrete dynamical systems and their symbolic representations. The paper specifically focuses on the factoring relation between subshifts and cellular automata, which falls under the category of discrete dynamical systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the notion of intrinsic universality, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of recursion theory in the paper suggests a connection to logic and computability theory (cs.LO), and the study of simulation relations in symbolic spaces is relevant to systems and control theory (cs.SY).
